# ⚙️ Step 1 — Install Apache

### RHEL / CentOS

```bash
sudo yum install -y httpd
```

Verify installation:

```bash
httpd -v
```

---

# ⚙️ Step 2 — Configure Apache Port

Open the Apache configuration file.

```bash
sudo vi /etc/httpd/conf/httpd.conf
```

Replace

```apache
Listen 80
```

with

```apache
Listen 8089
```

---

# 📦 Step 3 — Copy Website Files

The website backups are available on the **Jump Host**.

Copy them to **App Server 1**.

```bash
scp -r /home/thor/ecommerce tony@app01:/tmp/
scp -r /home/thor/cluster tony@app01:/tmp/
```

---

# 📁 Step 4 — Deploy Websites

```bash
sudo cp -r /tmp/ecommerce /var/www/html/
sudo cp -r /tmp/cluster /var/www/html/
```

Verify:

```bash
ls -l /var/www/html
```

Expected:

```text
ecommerce/
cluster/
```

---

# 🔐 Step 5 — Set Permissions

```bash
sudo chown -R apache:apache /var/www/html/ecommerce
sudo chown -R apache:apache /var/www/html/cluster

sudo chmod -R 755 /var/www/html/ecommerce
sudo chmod -R 755 /var/www/html/cluster
```

> **Ubuntu:** Replace `apache` with `www-data`.

---

# ▶️ Step 6 — Start Apache

```bash
sudo systemctl enable httpd
sudo systemctl restart httpd
```

Check status:

```bash
sudo systemctl status httpd
```

---

# 🌐 Step 7 — Verify Listening Port

```bash
sudo ss -tlnp | grep 8089
```

Expected:

```text
LISTEN 0 128 *:8089
```

---

# 🧪 Step 8 — Test the Websites

### Ecommerce

```bash
curl http://localhost:8089/ecommerce/
```

### Cluster

```bash
curl http://localhost:8089/cluster/
```

---

# 📋 Quick Commands

```bash
# Install Apache
sudo yum install -y httpd

# Configure Port
sudo sed -i 's/^Listen 80/Listen 8089/' /etc/httpd/conf/httpd.conf

# Deploy Websites
sudo cp -r /tmp/ecommerce /var/www/html/
sudo cp -r /tmp/cluster /var/www/html/

# Permissions
sudo chown -R apache:apache /var/www/html/{ecommerce,cluster}
sudo chmod -R 755 /var/www/html/{ecommerce,cluster}

# Start Apache
sudo systemctl enable httpd
sudo systemctl restart httpd

# Verify
curl http://localhost:8089/ecommerce/
curl http://localhost:8089/cluster/
```

